Easy Setup Guide

1. Use Python version `3.9.13`.

2. Install Tesseract OCR.
   Download from: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
   After installing, add `tesseract.exe` to your system PATH.

3. Check package compatibility first:
   `pip install -r .\requirements.txt --dry-run --ignore-installed`

4. Install required packages:
   `pip install -r .\requirements.txt`

5. Install Protobuf separately:
   `pip install protobuf==3.20.3`

6. Run the project:
   - Go to `./src/`
   - Run: `python main.py`
   - Enter a username to register face
   - Sit in good lighting
   - ALIGN your FACE into WHITE BOX Properly
   - Do not press any key during face registration , it Registers Automatically

7. Optional face registration method:
   You can also add a face image manually inside the `known_faces` folder.

8. If face authentication is not working:
   - Close the app
   - Run this command to start without face auth:
     `python main.py -fd`


Auto-Run EaseAccess at Windows Startup :

   a. press Win+R: 
   b. enter `taskschd.msc` and click OK.
   c. In the Task Scheduler window, click `Create Task` from the right-side panel.
   d. Enter a name for the task, such as `EaseAccess Startup`, then click `Run only when user is logged on`.
   e. Open the Triggers tab and click New, Choose `When I log on` as the trigger, click on `Any User` , Delay Task for `5 Seconds`, tick `Enabled` and then OK .
   f. Go to the Actions tab and click New, Select `Start a program` as the action.
   g. Browse and locate the pythonw.exe file in system, usually the file is at below location , but if not found, open CMD and run `where pythonw.exe`.
         -Make sure to have field locations as below ↴ 

                  Program/Script : `C:\Users\***username***\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python311\pythonw.exe` ~(pythonw.exe's path)
                  Arguments : `C:\abc\*\xyz\**\src\main.py -auto`    ~(main.py path with `-auto` flag as mentioned)
                  Starts In : `C:\abc\*\xyz\**\src`   ~(src folder's path)
   h. Goto Conditions Tab ,Untick the `Start Only if Computer is on AC Power`checkbox and Tick the `Start Only If Network Connnection is Available` checkbox and select `Any Connection` in dropdown .
   i. Review the settings and click Finish to save the task.
   j. Sign Out/Restart/Shutdown your computer to confirm that EaseAccess starts automatically at startup.
